    "id": "slide8",
    "eyebrow": "Political Context",
    "num": "08",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">08</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Political Context</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texicans Under Mexican Rule</h2><ul><li>Loyal to Mexican government but with local autonomy</li><li>Participated in provincial politics of Coahuila y Texas</li><li>Faced tensions with Anglo settlers and central authorities</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans were Mexican citizens who engaged in local governance but experienced growing tensions as Anglo immigration increased and political dynamics shifted. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican leaders serving in local councils balancing Mexican laws and frontier realities.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how Texicans navigated loyalty to Mexico amid changing political pressures.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texicans uniformly opposed Anglo settlers or Mexican authorities.</p></div></div>",
