    "eyebrow": "Activity",
    "num": "11",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">11</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Activity</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Analyzing Primary Source Excerpts on Texican Identity</h2><ul><li>Read excerpts defining 'Texican' from 1820s documents</li><li>Compare with later uses of 'Texian' and 'Texan'</li><li>Discuss how identity terms evolved over time</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This activity engages learners with original texts to explore how terms for Texas residents changed, reflecting shifting political and cultural realities. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Review a land grant calling a settler 'Texican' and a 1836 letter referring to 'Texians.'</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> What differences do you notice in how these terms are used? What might explain these changes?</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Taking terms at face value without considering historical context.</p></div></div>",
