    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">17</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texicans’ Role in Early Texas History</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texicans in Mexico-Spain Conflicts</h2><ul><li>Texicans were caught in the struggle between Mexico and Spain over Texas</li><li>They often had divided loyalties influenced by local interests</li><li>Their actions impacted territorial control and political developments</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">During the early 19th century, Texicans navigated the conflict between Mexico and Spain, sometimes supporting Mexican independence while also protecting local autonomy, reflecting complex political loyalties. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Some Texicans supported Mexican revolutionary forces against Spain, while others prioritized local defense against external threats.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Evaluate how Texican loyalties might shift based on political and economic pressures.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texicans uniformly supported one side oversimplifies their strategic choices.</p></div></div>",
