    "eyebrow": "Texicans’ Role in Early Texas History",
    "num": "19",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">19</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texicans’ Role in Early Texas History</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Role-Play Preparation: Texican Perspectives in the Texas Revolution</h2><ul><li>Learners will simulate Texican viewpoints during the revolution</li><li>Focus on cultural tensions, political loyalties, and personal stakes</li><li>Prepare arguments reflecting diverse Texican experiences</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Role-play helps learners embody Texican perspectives, exploring the nuanced cultural and political factors influencing their decisions during the Texas Revolution. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A learner might argue from the perspective of a Texican loyal to Mexico concerned about Anglo dominance and cultural loss.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Develop a position statement representing a Texican viewpoint on independence or loyalty to Mexico.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Oversimplifying Texican positions into pro- or anti-independence without cultural context.</p></div></div>",
