    "id": "slide32",
    "eyebrow": "Texicans’ Role in Early Texas History",
    "num": "20",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">20</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texicans’ Role in Early Texas History</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Role-Play Activity: Simulating Texican Loyalties</h2><ul><li>Engage in a debate representing different Texican positions</li><li>Explore cultural tensions between Mexican loyalty and Texan independence</li><li>Reflect on how identity influenced political choices</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This interactive role-play allows learners to actively debate Texican loyalties, deepening understanding of the cultural and political complexities during the Texas Revolution. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> One learner argues for maintaining Mexican ties to preserve culture; another advocates for independence to protect local autonomy.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Participate in the debate, using historical evidence to support your Texican position.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Allowing the debate to become polarized without acknowledging nuanced middle positions.</p></div></div>",
