    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">24</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice Checkpoint</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Evaluating Texican Loyalties: Reflection and Discussion</h2><ul><li>Consider the factors influencing Texican loyalties during Mexico-Spain conflicts and the Texas Revolution</li><li>Reflect on how cultural identity and political pressures shaped decisions</li><li>Discuss the implications for understanding early Texas history</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This reflective exercise encourages learners to synthesize knowledge of Texican loyalties and cultural influences, fostering deeper historical insight. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A Texican settler’s letter reveals conflicted feelings about independence and loyalty to Mexico.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief reflection on how Texican identity influenced their political choices and what this reveals about frontier history.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Oversimplifying loyalties as purely political without cultural context misses key motivations.</p></div></div>",
