    "num": "26",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">26</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Sources</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Legal Documents: Land Grants and Property Records</h2><ul><li>Land grants illustrate settlement patterns and economic activities</li><li>Show government policies and Texican responses</li><li>Reveal social status and family connections</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Legal documents such as land grants provide concrete evidence of where Texicans settled and how they established their livelihoods. These records also reflect Mexican government efforts to encourage colonization. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A land grant issued to a Texican family details acreage, location, and conditions for settlement.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze a land grant excerpt to determine what it reveals about Texican settlement priorities.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Do not overlook the legal language that may affect interpretation of rights and obligations.</p></div></div>",
