    "num": "27",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">27</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Sources</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Photographs and Visual Records of Texican Life</h2><ul><li>Visual sources capture material culture and environment</li><li>Include images of settlements, clothing, and community events</li><li>Help contextualize written records</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Photographs from Texican archives provide visual evidence of their lifestyle and surroundings. They complement textual sources by showing physical realities and cultural expressions. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A photograph of a Texican homestead illustrates architectural styles and land use.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Observe a photograph and describe what it reveals about Texican daily life and environment.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Avoid interpreting photos without considering the photographer’s intent and historical context.</p></div></div>",
