    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">32</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Research Skills</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Cross-Referencing Sources for Comprehensive Analysis</h2><ul><li>Use multiple source types to verify facts and perspectives</li><li>Identify consistencies and contradictions</li><li>Build a nuanced understanding of Texican history</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Combining letters, legal documents, and photographs allows for richer, more accurate historical interpretations. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Matching a letter’s description of a settlement with its land grant and a photograph of the area.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Compare two different source excerpts on the same event and note agreements and differences.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Relying on a single source type which may present a limited view.</p></div></div>",
