    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">36</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Summary</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Key Takeaways: Primary Sources and Texican History</h2><ul><li>Primary sources provide direct insight into Texican identity and experiences</li><li>Critical analysis requires evaluating authenticity, bias, and context</li><li>Combining letters, legal documents, and photographs enriches understanding</li><li>Skills developed are essential for nuanced historical interpretation and transfer</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This slide consolidates the main lessons from the primary source analysis section, reinforcing the importance of critical engagement with historical materials. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Reviewing how a combined analysis of a letter, land grant, and photograph reveals a complex picture of Texican life.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Reflect on how primary source analysis changed your understanding of Texicans.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Neglecting the interplay of different source types in constructing history.</p></div></div>",
