    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">42</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Group Discussion</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Discussing Common Misconceptions About Texican Identity</h2><ul><li>Texicans are often mistakenly seen as purely Mexican or Anglo settlers.</li><li>Indigenous influences are frequently overlooked or minimized.</li><li>Discuss how these misconceptions affect historical narratives.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Group discussion helps learners critically examine and challenge common misconceptions about Texican identity, promoting a more accurate and inclusive historical understanding (s2, s7, s10). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Some narratives ignore indigenous alliances, portraying Texicans as isolated European descendants.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> In groups, identify misconceptions and propose ways to correct them in historical accounts.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Accepting simplified or biased historical narratives without question.</p></div></div>",
