    "eyebrow": "Practice",
    "num": "44",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">44</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Practice: Creating a Texican Identity Profile</h2><ul><li>Use knowledge of etymology, indigenous influence, and cultural hybridity.</li><li>Describe key elements that define Texican identity.</li><li>Include linguistic, cultural, and historical factors.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This practice exercise encourages learners to synthesize information and articulate a comprehensive profile of Texican identity, reinforcing mastery (s2, s6, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A Texican identity profile might highlight indigenous linguistic roots, Mexican legal traditions, and frontier cultural exchanges.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief profile summarizing the defining characteristics of Texican identity.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Focusing only on one cultural influence or ignoring historical context.</p></div></div>",
